         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">13/6/93. ¶  ¶ You will receive, dear M. de Candolle, an official message, conveyed by the hon Secr. of the Field-Naturalists Club of Victoria, expressive of our grief at the loss of your  ¶ uncomparab...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.06.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Casimir de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by de Candolle: 'répondu 25,7,93 annoncé envoi de portrait et dit que les Myoporines <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">seront les bien venues</hi>
                     </seg> après l'Impression des Guttifères' [answered 25.7.93. Announced sending of a portrait and said that the <name key="Myoporinae">Myoporinae</name> would be welcome after the printing of the Guttiferae]. Letter not found; M acknowledged receipt of both the letter and the portrait in M to C. de Candolle, 4 September 1893.</p>
               </note>13/6/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will receive, dear M. de Candolle, an official message, conveyed by the hon Secr. of the Field-Naturalists Club of Victoria, expressive of our grief at the loss of your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">uncomparable</hi>
               </seg> father.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The message was apparently accompanied by a copy of M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">éloge</seg> of Alphonse de Candolle, read to the Victorian Field Naturalists' Club at its meeting on 8 May 1893; see B93.06.04 and M to C. de Candolle, 4 September 1893.</p>
               </note> Last evening, when distributing as Patron the annual prizes at the Club to 6 juvenile Ladies and 7 young Gentlemen, for the field-work and collections emanating therefrom,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Victorian naturalist</seg>, vol. 10 (1893), pp. 43-4.</p>
               </note> I alluded to the Australian Bellflower, <name key="Wahlenbergia%20gracilis">Wahlenbergia gracilis</name>, as our floral souvenir for ever of your parent, it being the only species here, which may form a blue sheet on our meadows, the blue as a prevailing color hardly anywhere existing here in any places of vegetation, though often met with in Europe through the many campanulas.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Wahlenbergia%20gracilis">Wahlenbergia gracilis</name>
                     </seg> was named by Alphonse de Candolle.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Enclosed you will also find find<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word repeated.</p>
               </note> a condolatory letter from young Naturalist-boys, who on their spontaneous impulse send this tégmoinage<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>testimony.</p>
               </note> of their sorrow, when they heard of Alphonse de Candolle's passing away through me, and in a similar manner will likely be sent to you condolatory adresses also from other science unions in the Australian Colonies. Your worthy mother must have come from a family, originating in Germany, according to her maiden name.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Casimir de Candolle's mother's maiden name was Kunkler.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever with regardful attachment your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I feel sure you will honor our Club and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">also</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">the juvenile</hi>
               </seg> "Field-Club of Surrey-Hills"<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic. The Surrey Hills Field Club was 'established by a few enthusiasts for directing the attention of the young people of one of our suburbs to natural history' (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Vic. naturalist</seg>, vol. 10 [1893], p. 30).</p>
               </note> with some few encouraging lines.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I must try to redeem early my promise to furnish the <name key="Myoporinae">Myoporinae</name> for the "Monogr. phanerog." The delay has much enriched the material, particularly from new regions in Central Austr.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's promised systematic work on the <name key="Myoporinae">Myoporinae</name> for A. de Candolle &amp; C. de Candolle (1878-96) never appeared.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Myoporinae">Myoporinae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Wahlenbergia%20gracilis">Wahlenbergia gracilis</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
